.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm __os_mutex_* ,
.Nm __os_rwlock_* ,
.Nm __os_cond_* ,
and
.Nm __os_sem_*
families are the BDB-style portable wrappers around pthread mutexes,
rwlocks, condition variables, and POSIX semaphores.
.Pp
The handle types
.Vt __os_mutex_t , Vt __os_rwlock_t , Vt __os_cond_t ,
and
.Vt __os_sem_t
contain inline storage sized to comfortably hold the platform's
underlying type, so no separate allocation is required at init time.
.Pp
.Fn __os_mutex_trylock
returns
.Dv XTC_E_AGAIN
when the mutex is already held by another thread; the same convention
applies to
.Fn __os_sem_trywait .
.Pp
.Fn __os_cond_wait
must be called with
.Fa m
held; on return
.Fa m
is held again.
Spurious wakeups are possible per the underlying pthread contract;
callers must re-check the predicate in a
.Sy while
loop.
.Pp
.Fn __os_sem_*
implements an unnamed in-process semaphore.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
.Dv XTC_OK
on success;
.Dv XTC_E_INVAL
on a NULL handle;
.Dv XTC_E_AGAIN
when a try-style lock is already held;
.Dv XTC_E_INTERNAL
on platform failure.
.Sh THREAD SAFETY
All operations are safe to call from any thread.
A handle must be initialised before use and destroyed after the last
operation completes.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr __os_atomic 3 ,
